definition[0]_en: A flat piece of thin material (paper, plastic, etc.). (Deprecated)

A unit of extent of text that is a container for holding loose materials (e.g., paintings, drawings, papers, unbound sections of a book, and similar materials) usually consisting of two covers joined together at the back. (Deprecated)
A box containing bound or unbound resources. (Deprecated)
One or more sheets bound or fastened together to form a single unit. (Deprecated)
